# SDD Step 1 — Specify Feature

Create `specs/NNN-<feature-slug>/spec.md` for this request:
> Allow users to view and place orders

Project: shopping-app
Stack: Dart / Flutter | Platform: Cross-platform

## Instructions
1. Derive a feature slug from the description using kebab-case.
2. Scan `specs/` to find the next feature number.
3. Create `specs/NNN-<feature-slug>/` and any needed subdirectories.
4. Save the following template as `spec.md`.

```md
# Feature Spec: <feature title>
- Project: shopping-app
- Stack: Dart / Flutter (Cross-platform)
- Feature Number: NNN
- Branch: NNN-<feature-slug>
- Status: DRAFT

## §1 Problem Statement
Derive the problem statement from the user description. State the user pain, business need, and desired outcome.

## §2 User Stories
- As a <role>, I want <action>, so that <benefit>
- Derive all stories from the description.
- If any role, action, constraint, or expected outcome is ambiguous, mark it inline with:
  [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: <specific question>]

## §3 Acceptance Criteria
For each user story, write Given / When / Then criteria.
Every unknown must be marked with [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: <specific question>].

## §4 Non-Functional Requirements
| Category | Requirement |
|----------|-------------|
| Performance | [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: What response time or interaction latency is acceptable?] |
| Offline | [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: Must this feature work without network connectivity?] |
| Platform | [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: Are there iOS-specific or Android-specific behaviors?] |
| Data retention | [NEEDS CLARIFICATION: How long must local data be retained?] |

## §5 Out of Scope
List explicitly what is NOT included in this feature.

## §6 Open Questions
List every [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] marker collected from the sections above.
```

## Critical Rules
- ✅ Focus on WHAT and WHY
- ❌ Never mention widgets, components, HTTP endpoints, databases, or frameworks in the spec body
- ✅ Mark every ambiguity with `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION: <specific question>]`

## Gate
Count all `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION]` markers.
- If count > 0 → call `spec_clarify`
- If count = 0 → call `spec_plan`
